Aren't we fans of ideas that make the world a better place to live in for ALL?! 😅

IKEA created add-ons to use with their most iconic products, each solving a different accessibility problem. From sofa elevating legs for easier ascend and lamp button-enlargement to super-zipper for pillows-covers, the brand is helping people with disabilities to live a normal life in their own homes.🙌

#socialmediadissect #ikea #advertising #marketing #brandidentity

When you give someone a good news, something celebratory with it makes it 10 times better and Google got the trick! ✨😅

Try it out for yourself and tell us what you think in the comments below. 💬

Is this a coincidence or an expensive rip off of concept by @upgrad_edu of @toothsi_aligners's ad? 

Toothsi’s angry actor and 'humare samay mein yeh sab kyu nhi tha' concept is strikingly similar to that of Upgrads. With bigger budgets and slight twist in execution Upgrad might have created more impact. But did they  lack a unique sentiment or just got little too inspired? What say? 

To see our take on it, click on the link in our bio! 

#socialmediadissect #toothsi #upgrad #gandicopy #advertisement

Here’s Lifebuoy showing life saviour behaviour! 😅🤌

The ad was created for the Ministry of School Education Punjab to promote gender equality in schools in Pakistan, where there is only 7% female representation in the curriculum. The campaign 'Mein Choti Si Aik Ladki Hoon' (I am a little girl) has started a movement and inspired policymakers to revise the curriculum to a more balanced syllabi.

Lifebuoy Shampoo and GREY Pakistan began the effort by revisiting Jameeludin Aali's renowned children's rhyme, which is narrated from a male perspective to now in a female’s voice. 

#socialmediadissect #womenempowerment #lifebuoy #girlseducation #advertising

@shapoorjipallonjirealestate took to the streets of Thane to create India's first 4D billboard. 

Trying to bring back the concept of balconies in Mumbai's suburbs, the brand decided to create something people have never experienced before! 

You can see lifestyle influencers practicing yoga, playing golf, and enjoying their coffee live on the billboard. With this 4D outdoor advertising campaign, Shapoorji Pallonji gained a lot of attention and we would say they deserved it.

#socialmediadissect #collab #shapoorjipallonji #billboard #advertising

Society: We support independent women, *whispers under their breath* selectively. 👀

Here's a 53-year-old luggage brand portraying modern liberalism through a traditional wedding setting of aunties sharing blessings. 

With their #PyarWahiSochNayi campaign, @vipbagsindia makes the most of the wedding occasion to spread the right message and we are in for that!💯

@_vaanikapoor_ 

#VIPWeddingFavourites2022 #PyaarWahiSochNayi #VIPBags #socialmediadissect #collab

Viewing tempting food while fasting requires a whole lot of patience 🥵
This innovative digital #billboard by @tescofood shows empty plates that fascinatingly fill up with food as the sun sets and it’s time for Muslims to open their fast. 

Their message- ‘In honour of everyone fasting, these plates only fill up as the sun goes down.’

Kudos to team @bbhlondon on this creative #OOH campaign. 

#SocialMediaDissect #Ramadan #Festive #Digital #OfflineMarketing

Google has changed its ‘G’ logo for the first time in almost 10 years. 

The new logo has blended colors instead of sharp color borders, giving it a smooth, gradient look like the logo used for Google’s Gemini AI. 

Right now, this new logo is only seen on iPhones and Pixel phones.

@anna_mariya_justine_ posted a video where she appears to charge her phone using two potatoes and a coin, which is scientifically impossible. 

While the video shows the phone as charging, it doesn’t clearly reveal whether the wire is actually connected to the potatoes. 

Is it okay to mislead the audience in the name of creating content?

#FakeLand #Phone #Charging #Misleading #Content #SocialMediaDissect
